title: Casualty Ward: Who is set to miss pre-season?
text:
Mark Blicavs (knee) — 2-3 weeks (played in recent intra-club) 
Josh Cowan (hamstring) — 1-2 weeks (played in recent intra-club) 
Cory Gregson (foot) — 8-10 weeks 
Daniel Menzel (knee) — ongoing (managed through JLT, will miss JLT1) 
Esava Ratugolea (calf/Achilles) — 2 weeks 
GOLD COAST SUNS 
Gary Ablett (shoulder) — 4 weeks (available for JLT3) 
Jarrod Harbrow (ankle) — 6-8 weeks (unlikely for Round 1) 
Michael Rischitelli (ACL) — 3 months (aiming at return in first half of season) 
Tom Nicholls (calf) — 1-2 weeks (increasing training workload) Gary Ablett is likely to return to action in the Gold Coast Suns’ third JLT Community Series game. Photo: Regi Varghese Source: News Corp Australia 
GWS GIANTS 
Brett Deledio (calf) — 3-5 weeks (aiming at JLT3) 
Steve Johnson (thumb) — 1-2 weeks 
Shane Mumford (elbow) — 2-3 weeks (aiming at JLT2) 
Dylan Shiel (ankle) — 1-2 weeks 
HAWTHORN 
Jon Ceglar (ACL) — 6 months 
MELBOURNE 
Ben Kennedy (ankle) — 2-3 weeks (may miss JLT) 
Dean Kent (back) — 2-3 weeks (likely to miss JLT) 
Dom Tyson (knee) — 2-3 weeks 
NORTH MELBOURNE 
Jed Anderson (AC joint) — 4-6 weeks (aiming at VFL Round 1) 
Ben Brown (knee) — 5 weeks (aiming at Round 1) 
Majak Daw (knee) — 3 weeks (aiming at JLT3) 
Taylor Garner (hip) — 7 weeks 
Todd Goldstein (ankle) — 3 weeks (aiming at JLT3) 
Ben Jacobs (foot) — 3 weeks (aiming at JLT2) 
Oscar Junker (broken tibia) — 3-4 months 
Daniel Nielson (quad) — 3 weeks (aiming at JLT2) 
Jy Simpkin (broken leg) — 3 weeks (aiming at JLT2) 
Sam Wright (ankles) — 5 weeks (aiming at JLT3) Todd Goldstein is set to miss most of the JLT Community Series. (Photo by Michael Willson/AFL Media/Getty Images) Source: Getty Images 
PORT ADELAIDE 
Dougal Howard (ACL) — 2-4 months 
Angus Monfries (shoulder) — four weeks (available for JLT 3) 
Jesse Palmer (groin) — 2-3 weeks (available for Round 1) 
RICHMOND 
Jack Graham (hamstring) — 1-2 weeks 
Steven Morris (ACL) — 3-4 months 
Dion Prestia (knee) — 2-3 weeks (played in recent intra-club) 
ST KILDA 
Hugh Goddard (Achilles) — 2-3 months 
SYDNEY SWANS 
Alex Johnson (knee/hamstring) — 2-3 weeks 
Jeremy Laidler (elbow) — 3-4 weeks (likely to miss JLT) 
Tom Papley (knee) — 7 weeks (on long-term injury list until at least Round 2) 
Luke Parker (knee) — 1-2 weeks (aiming at JLT2) 
Callum Sinclair (knee) — 2 weeks (aiming at JLT2) 
Dean Towers (appendix) — 1 week (aiming at JLT1) 
WEST COAST EAGLES 
Liam Duggan (hamstring) — 1-2 weeks (likely to miss JLT1) 
Scott Lycett (PCL) — 4-6 weeks (aiming at JLT3) 
Nic Naitanui (ACL) — 5-6 months (would return late in season if at all in 2017) 
Willie Rioli (hamstring) — 3 months 
Simon Tunbridge (ACL) — 4 months (aiming at mid-season) 
WESTERN BULLDOGS 
Kieran Collins (shoulder/hip) — 1-2 weeks 
Caleb Daniel (shoulder) — 2-3 weeks (aiming at JLT2) 
Josh Prudden (ACL) — 2 months (should miss JLT) 
Matt Suckling (Achilles) — 4-6 weeks (may not play JLT) 
Jack Redpath (ACL) — 3-4 months (aiming at mid-season) 
Mitch Wallis (broken leg) — TBC (has begun running)
